{
  "doc_id": "49713",
  "text": "When a cystic mass is evaluated, a surgical cyst can be suspected only if enhancement is present. Calcification in a cystic renal mass is not as important in diagnosis as the presence of associated enhancing soft-tissue elements [CITATION_1] . MR imaging may depict additional septa, thickening of the wall and/or septa, or enhancement, which may lead to an upgraded Bosniak cyst classification and can affect case management [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
